observations.recommendation:
4.10. We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to require the
following:
a) BAC to submit the missing attachments;
b) BAC Secretariat to issue notification letter to all losing bidders;
c) BAC to invite three observers during post-qualification at least five
days before the procurement activity;
d) Project Engineer to adopt the prescribed format of Approved
Contract in DPWH D.O. 197 series 2016;
e) BAC Secretariat to attach a snapshot as proof of sending the
invitation to Observers; and
f) BAC Secretariat to properly mark/stamp the month, date and year
when the bidder submit other supporting documents as required in
the 2016 Revised IRR of RA 9184.

We recommended and Management agreed to direct the BAC to:

submit  the missing attachments of the awarded contracts and the bid documents, minutes and other pertinent documents from the proceedings of the failed bidding;

require attachment of photocopy of Official Receipt for payment of bidding documents when bidder/s submit their Bidding documents;

invite COA representative, private group representative and NGO representative at least five calendar days before the date of eligibility checking, shortlisting, pre-bid conference, preliminary examination of bids, bid evaluation, and post-qualification;

 conduct pre-procurement conference as required by the IRR; and

 adopt the prescribed format of Approved Contract in DPWH D.O. 197 series 2016;

We further recommended that the Municipal Engineer prepare and include PERT/CPM as part of the contract to be submitted to the Audit Team.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Require the Municipal Engineering Office to expedite the preparation of POW of the planned development programs;
Advise the BAC to fast track the bidding and procurement process of the unimplemented projects and the issuance of Notice to Proceed;
Instruct the concerned Municipal Officials to closely monitor the implementation of the identified development projects especially those from previous years’ budgets; and
Ensure that the development projects are completed within the timetable set.

We recommended Management the following:
Exert all efforts to collect the receivables  account to the concerned debtors/persons liable by sending them Demand Letters or follow-up letters; 

File the necessary request for the write-off of dormant receivables that are deemed uncollectible complete with supporting documents evidencing that efforts to collect the same were made ; 

Diligently make efforts to locate the necessary supporting documents establish the existence and validity for claiming the receivables and to cause their collection; and

Advise the Municipal Accountant to provide Allowance for Impairment for the receivables account so as to present fairly the proper valuation of their net realizable value, and, adjust its effect to the equity account.

We recommended Management to require the General Services Office the following:

Conduct  physical count  of  Inventory items semestrally and prepare a RPCI and submit to the Auditor not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively;

Perform semestral reconciliation of the RCPI with the balance of the Inventory account as recorded by the Municipal Accounting Office.

We recommend and Management agreed to enjoin all the offices’ concerned strict compliance to the accounting and reporting guidelines on the Local Roads Assets Management System prescribed by COA Circular 2015-008 to:
a. provide complete description of the road and its components in the reports prepared by the MAccO and the property office;
b. reconcile subsidiary ledgers with the Local Road Inventory and Road Map to ensure completeness and accuracy of the LRN account;
c. prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation of each depreciable LRN component; and
d. include a full disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements with regards to the LRN account.
